routingIpv6.name: routingIpv6
routingIpv6.contactinfo: Customer Support Postal: Quanta Computer Inc. 4, Wen Ming 1 St., Kuei Shan Hsiang, Tao Yuan Shien, Taiwan, R.O.C. Tel: +886 3 328 0050 E-Mail: strong.chen@quantatw.com
routingIpv6.description: The Quanta Private MIB for FastPath Ipv6 Routing

SpfTimerRange.name: SpfTimerRange
SpfTimerRange.description: The range of intervals on which Spf timers can be configured.

AutoCostRefBw.name: AutoCostRefBw
AutoCostRefBw.description: The value of reference bandwidth from which ospf calculates metric cost.

agentIpv6RoutingMode.name: agentIpv6RoutingMode
agentIpv6RoutingMode.description: Administratively enables/disables ipv6 unicast routing on the switch.

agentIpv6InterfaceIfIndex.name: agentIpv6InterfaceIfIndex
agentIpv6InterfaceIfIndex.description: The IfIndex associated with this instance.

agentIpv6InterfaceMtuValue.name: agentIpv6InterfaceMtuValue
agentIpv6InterfaceMtuValue.description: Configures the MTU value for this interface.If it is not yet configured, retrieving the value of this object results in a zero value. Setting the value zero to this object effectively un-configures the MTU.

agentIpv6InterfaceDadTransmits.name: agentIpv6InterfaceDadTransmits
agentIpv6InterfaceDadTransmits.description: Configures the dad transmits value for this interface.

agentIpv6InterfaceLinkLocalOnly.name: agentIpv6InterfaceLinkLocalOnly
agentIpv6InterfaceLinkLocalOnly.description: When enabled, interface is capable of ipv6 operation without a global address. In this case, an eui-64 based link-local address is used.

agentIpv6InterfaceIcmpUnreachables.name: agentIpv6InterfaceIcmpUnreachables
agentIpv6InterfaceIcmpUnreachables.description: If this object is enable, it indicates that ICMPv6 unreachables can be sent on this interface.

agentIpv6InterfaceAutoconfig.name: agentIpv6InterfaceAutoconfig
agentIpv6InterfaceAutoconfig.description: If this object is enabled, it indicates that the IPv6 address is automatically generated using IPv6 stateless address auto configuration.

agentIpv6InterfaceDhcpClient.name: agentIpv6InterfaceDhcpClient
agentIpv6InterfaceDhcpClient.description: If this object is enabled, the interface uses DHCPv6 Client protocol to acquire an IPv6 address.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementTable.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementTable
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementTable.description: There is no global administrative flag for router advertisement. The global routing flag (agentIpv6RoutingMode) will be used for this purpose. If routing is disabled, router advertisement is disabled as well.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementIfIndex.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementIfIndex
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementIfIndex.description: Interface Number to configure Router Advertisement on.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementSuppressMode.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementSuppressMode
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementSuppressMode.description: Enable or disable router advertisement suppression on the interface.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMaxAdvertise.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMaxAdvertisementInterval
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMaxAdvertise.description: Maximum time allowed between sending router advertisements from the interface. (Max * 0.75 >= Min)

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMinAdvertise.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMinAdvertisementInterval
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMinAdvertise.description: Mimimum time allowed between sending router advertisements from the interface. (Max * 0.75 >= Min)

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementAdvertisemen.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementAdvertisementLifetime
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementAdvertisemen.description: Value of lifetime field of router advertisement sent from the interface. This value must be greater than or equal to agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMaxAdvertisementInterval.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementNbrSolicitIn.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementNbrSolicitInterval
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementNbrSolicitIn.description: Value of retrans time field of router advertisement sent from the interface. A value of 0 means this router does not specifiy the interval. The valid value range is 1000..4294967295

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementReachableTim.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementReachableTime
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementReachableTim.description: Value of reachable time field of router advertisement sent from the interface. A value of 0 means this router does not specifiy the interval.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementManagedFlag.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementManagedFlag
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementManagedFlag.description: Value of managed config field of router advertisement sent from the interface.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementOtherFlag.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementOtherFlag
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementOtherFlag.description: Value of other config field of router advertisement sent from the interface.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixTable.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixTable
agentIpv6AddrPrefixTable.description: The list of IPv6 address prefixes of IPv6 interfaces.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixEntry.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixEntry
agentIpv6AddrPrefixEntry.description: An interface entry containing objects of a particular IPv6 address prefix.

agentIpv6AddrPrefix.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefix
agentIpv6AddrPrefix.description: The prefix associated with the this interface.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixLength.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixLength
agentIpv6AddrPrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix (in bits).

agentIpv6AddrPrefixOnLinkFlag.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixOnLinkFlag
agentIpv6AddrPrefixOnLinkFlag.description: This object has the value 'true(1)', if this prefix can be used for on-link determination and the value 'false(2)' otherwise.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixAutonomousFlag.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixAutonomousFlag
agentIpv6AddrPrefixAutonomousFlag.description: Autonomous address configuration flag. When true(1), indicates that this prefix can be used for autonomous address configuration (i.e. can be used to form a local interface address). If false(2), it is not used to autoconfigure a local interface address.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvPreferredLifetime.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvPreferredLifetime
agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvPreferredLifetime.description: It is the length of time in seconds that this prefix will remain preferred, i.e. time until deprecation. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity. The address generated from a deprecated prefix should no longer be used as a source address in new communications, but packets received on such an interface are processed as expected.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvValidLifetime.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvValidLifetime
agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvValidLifetime.description: It is the length of time in seconds that this prefix will remain valid, i.e. time until invalidation. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity. The address generated from an invalidated prefix should not appear as the destination or source address of a packet.

agentIpv6AddrTable.name: agentIpv6AddrTable
agentIpv6AddrTable.description: The table of addressing information relevant to this node's interface addresses.

agentIpv6AddrEntry.name: agentIpv6AddrEntry
agentIpv6AddrEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this node's interface addresses.

agentIpv6AddrAddress.name: agentIpv6AddrAddress
agentIpv6AddrAddress.description: The IPv6 address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

agentIpv6AddrPfxLength.name: agentIpv6AddrPfxLength
agentIpv6AddrPfxLength.description: The length of the prefix (in bits) associated with the IPv6 address of this entry.

agentIpv6AddrEui64Flag.name: agentIpv6AddrEui64Flag
agentIpv6AddrEui64Flag.description: This object has the value 'true(1)', if this address uses and eui-64 generated interface identifier and the value 'false(2)' otherwise.

agentIpv6AddrStatus.name: agentIpv6AddrStatus
agentIpv6AddrStatus.description: Creates a new entry in the Address table. Allowed values are: createAndGo(4) - Creates an entry in this table, associating the address with a given interface. The agentIpv6NetMask object must be set during creation. destroy(6) - Removes the associated address from the interface.

agentIpv6StaticRouteTable.name: agentIpv6StaticRouteTable
agentIpv6StaticRouteTable.description: IPv6 Static Routing table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 static unicast route that can be used for packet forwarding determination.

agentIpv6StaticRouteDest.name: agentIpv6StaticRouteDest
agentIpv6StaticRouteDest.description: The destination IPv6 address of this route. This object may not take a Multicast address value.

agentIpv6StaticRoutePfxLength.name: agentIpv6StaticRoutePfxLength
agentIpv6StaticRoutePfxLength.description: Indicates the prefix length of the destination address.

agentIpv6StaticRouteIfIndex.name: agentIpv6StaticRouteIfIndex
agentIpv6StaticRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ipv6IfIndex. For routes with global address next hop this value can be zero.

agentIpv6StaticRouteNextHop.name: agentIpv6StaticRouteNextHop
agentIpv6StaticRouteNextHop.description: The address of the next system en route.

agentIpv6StaticRoutePreference.name: agentIpv6StaticRoutePreference
agentIpv6StaticRoutePreference.description: The routing preference metric for this route. A lower value is more preferred.

agentIpv6StaticRouteStatus.name: agentIpv6StaticRouteStatus
agentIpv6StaticRouteStatus.description: Creates a new entry in the Address table. Allowed values are: createAndGo(4) - Creates an entry in this table. destroy(6) - Removes the associated route from the interface.

agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixTable.name: agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixTable
agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixTable.description: IPv6 Service Port Prefix Table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 prefix configured on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixEntry.name: agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixEntry
agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixEntry.description: An IPv6 Service Port Prefix entry.

agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixIndex.name: agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixIndex
agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixIndex.description: The index of the Ipv6 Prefix Address configured on the Service Port. Removal of a row will cause index values to be reassigned.

agentIpv6ServicePortPrefix.name: agentIpv6ServicePortPrefix
agentIpv6ServicePortPrefix.description: The Ipv6 Prefix Address configured on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixLength.name: agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixLength
agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixLength.description: The length of the IPv6 Prefix Address.

agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterTable.name: agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterTable
agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterTable.description: IPv6 Service Port Default Router Table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 Default Router configured on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterEntry.name: agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterEntry
agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterEntry.description: An IPv6 Service Port Default Router entry.

agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterIndex.name: agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterIndex
agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterIndex.description: The index of the IPv6 Default Router Address configured on the Service Port. Removal of a row will cause index values to be reassigned.

agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouter.name: agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouter
agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouter.description: The Address of the IPv6 Default Router configured on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrTable.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrTable
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrTable.description: IPv6 Service Port Neighbor Table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 Neighbor configured on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrEntry.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrEntry
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrEntry.description: An IPv6 Service Port Neighbor entry.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrAddr.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrAddr
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrAddr.description: The Ipv6 Address of a neighbor switch visible to the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrPhysAddr.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrPhysAddr
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrPhysAddr.description: The MacAddress of the neighboring switch.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrState.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrState
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrState.description: The state of the neighboring switch: reachable(1) - The neighbor is reachable by this switch. stale(2) - Information about the neighbor is scheduled for deletion. delay(3) - No information has been received from neighbor during delay period. probe(4) - Switch is attempting to probe for this neighbor. unknown(6) - Unknown status.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrUpdated.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrUpdated
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrUpdated.description: The last sysUpTime that this neighbor has been updated.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrIsRouter.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrIsRouter
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrIsRouter.description: Returns true(1) if the neighbor machine is a router, false(2) otherwise.

agentIpv6ServicePortConfigProtocol.name: agentIpv6ServicePortConfigProtocol
agentIpv6ServicePortConfigProtocol.description: The switch's ServicePort IPv6 config protocol

agentIpv6ServicePortDhcpRestart.name: agentIpv6ServicePortDhcpRestart
agentIpv6ServicePortDhcpRestart.description: The switch's ServicePort IPv6 DHCP Restart

agentIpv6NeighborTable.name: agentIpv6NeighborTable
agentIpv6NeighborTable.description: IPv6 Neighbor Table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 Neighbor configured

agentIpv6NeighborIfIndex.name: agentIpv6NeighborIfIndex
agentIpv6NeighborIfIndex.description: A unique non-zero value identifying the particular IPv6 interface.

agentIpv6NeighborAddress.name: agentIpv6NeighborAddress
agentIpv6NeighborAddress.description: The Ipv6 Address of a neighbor switch visible

agentIpv6NeighborMacAddress.name: agentIpv6NeighborMacAddress
agentIpv6NeighborMacAddress.description: The MacAddress of the neighboring switch.

agentIpv6NeighborIsRouter.name: agentIpv6NeighborIsRouter
agentIpv6NeighborIsRouter.description: Returns true(1) if the neighbor machine is a router, false(2) otherwise.

agentIpv6NeighborState.name: agentIpv6NeighborState
agentIpv6NeighborState.description: The state of the neighboring switch: reachable(1) - The neighbor is reachable by this switch. stale(2) - Information about the neighbor is scheduled for deletion. delay(3) - No information has been received from neighbor during delay period. probe(4) - Switch is attempting to probe for this neighbor. unknown(6) - Unknown status.

agentIpv6NeighborLastUpdated.name: agentIpv6NeighborLastUpdated
agentIpv6NeighborLastUpdated.description: The last sysUpTime that this neighbor has been updated.

agentIpv6StaticNeighbor.name: agentIpv6StaticNeighbor
agentIpv6StaticNeighbor.description: IPv6 static Neighbor Table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 static Neighbor configured

agentIpv6StaticNeighborIfIndex.name: agentIpv6StaticNeighborIfIndex
agentIpv6StaticNeighborIfIndex.description: A unique non-zero value identifying the particular IPv6 interface.

agentIpv6StaticNeighborAddress.name: agentIpv6StaticNeighborAddress
agentIpv6StaticNeighborAddress.description: The Ipv6 Address of a static neighbor switch visible

agentIpv6StaticNeighborMacAddress.name: agentIpv6StaticNeighborMacAddress
agentIpv6StaticNeighborMacAddress.description: The MacAddress of the static neighboring switch.

agentIpv6StaticNeighborRowAddress.name: agentIpv6StaticNeighborRowAddress
agentIpv6StaticNeighborRowAddress.description: The Ipv6 Address of a static neighbor switch visible

agentIpv6StaticNeighborRowMacAddress.name: agentIpv6StaticNeighborRowMacAddress
agentIpv6StaticNeighborRowMacAddress.description: The MacAddress of the static neighboring switch.

agentIpv6StaticNeighborRowStatus.name: agentIpv6StaticNeighborRowStatus
agentIpv6StaticNeighborRowStatus.description: Creates a new entry in the Neighbor table. Allowed values are: createAndGo(4) - Creates an entry in this table. destroy(6) - Removes the associated address from the interface.

agentRouterRipngAdminState.name: agentRouterRipngAdminState
agentRouterRipngAdminState.description: Sets the administrative mode of RIPng in the router.

agentRouterRipngSplitHorizonMode.name: agentRouterRipngSplitHorizonMode
agentRouterRipngSplitHorizonMode.description: Sets the RIPng split horizon operating mode in the router. A value of none(1) means split horizon processing is disabled. When set to simple(2), the simple split horizon technique is used. When set to poisonReverse(3), the split horizon with poison reverse technique is used. The default split horizon mode is simple(2).

agentRouterRipngDefaultMetric.name: agentRouterRipngDefaultMetric
agentRouterRipngDefaultMetric.description: Default metric of redistributed routes, when RIPng redistributes from other protocols. {0} indicates that the parameter is not configured, this value should not be set. Valid range for set is (1..15).

agentRouterRipngDefaultMetricConfigured.name: agentRouterRipngDefaultMetricConfigured
agentRouterRipngDefaultMetricConfigured.description: Flag to determine whether RIPng default-metric is configured or not. Set to 'false' to unconfigure the default route metric. Set to 'true' is not allowed.

agentRouterRipngDefaultInfoOriginate.name: agentRouterRipngDefaultInfoOriginate
agentRouterRipngDefaultInfoOriginate.description: Flag to determine, whether RIPng can advertise a default-route learned from another protocol.

agentRouterRipngDistance.name: agentRouterRipngDistance
agentRouterRipngDistance.description: Configure the distance value for RIPng routes.

agentRipngRouteRedistTable.name: agentRipngRouteRedistTable
agentRipngRouteRedistTable.description: This table contains the MIB objects required to configure route-redistribution for RIPng. Here, RIPng is the Destination protocol and the source protocols can be any of : BGP, OSPF, Static, Connected.

agentRipngRouteRedistSource.name: agentRipngRouteRedistSource
agentRipngRouteRedistSource.description: Source route, from which RIPng can redistribute routes. This object also acts as the identifier for the RIP redistribution Table entry.

agentRipngRouteRedistMode.name: agentRipngRouteRedistMode
agentRipngRouteRedistMode.description: User enabels/disables route-redistribution for a particular source protocol.

agentRipngRouteRedistMetric.name: agentRipngRouteRedistMetric
agentRipngRouteRedistMetric.description: Metric used for redistributing a particular source protocol route into RIPng. {0} indicates that the parameter is not configured, this value should not be set. Valid range for set is (1..15).

agentRipngRouteRedistMetricConfigured.name: agentRipngRouteRedistMetricConfigured
agentRipngRouteRedistMetricConfigured.description: Flag to determine whether RIPng redistribute-metric is configured or not. Set to 'false' to unconfigure redistribute metric. Set to 'true' is not allowed.

agentRipngIfTable.name: agentRipngIfTable
agentRipngIfTable.description: The Ripng Interface Table describes the inter- faces from the viewpoint of Ripng.

agentRipngIfEntry.name: agentRipngIfEntry
agentRipngIfEntry.description: The Ripng Interface Entry describes one inter- face from the viewpoint of Ripng.

agentRipngIfIndex.name: agentRipngIfIndex
agentRipngIfIndex.description: The IfIndex associated with this instance.

agentRipngIfPassiveMode.name: agentRipngIfPassiveMode
agentRipngIfPassiveMode.description: Flag to determine whether the interface is passive. A passive interface will not participate in the Ripng adjacency formation.

agentOspfv3DefaultMetric.name: agentOspfv3DefaultMetric
agentOspfv3DefaultMetric.description: Default metric of redistributed routes, when OSPFv3 redistributes from other protocols.

agentOspfv3DefaultMetricConfigured.name: agentOspfv3DefaultMetricConfigured
agentOspfv3DefaultMetricConfigured.description: Flag to determine whether OSPFv3 default-metric is configured or not.

agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginate.name: agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginate
agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginate.description: Flag to determine, whether OSPFv3 can advertise a default-route learned from another protocol.

agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateAlways.name: agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateAlways
agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateAlways.description: When this flag is true, the router advertises 0.0.0.0/0.0.0.0 always. Without this option, OSPF will only advertise 0.0.0.0/0.0.0.0 if the router's forwarding table contains a default route.

agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateMetric.name: agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateMetric
agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateMetric.description: Metric of the default route,which OSPF advertises when learned from other protocol.

agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateMetricCon.name: agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateMetricConfigured
agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateMetricCon.description: Flag to determine whether OSPF default-info originate metric is configured or not.

agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateMetricTyp.name: agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateMetricType
agentOspfv3DefaultInfoOriginateMetricTyp.description: Metric Type of the default route,which OSPF advertises when learned from other protocol. It can be 1(external type 1) or 2(external type 2).

agentOspfv3RouteRedistTable.name: agentOspfv3RouteRedistTable
agentOspfv3RouteRedistTable.description: This table contains the MIB objects required to configure route-redistribution for OSPF. Here, OSPF is the Destination protocol and the source protocols can be any of : BGP, RIP, Static, Connected.

agentOspfv3RouteRedistSource.name: agentOspfv3RouteRedistSource
agentOspfv3RouteRedistSource.description: Source protocol, from which OSPF can redistribute routes. This object also acts as the identifier for the OSPF redistribution Table entry.

agentOspfv3RouteRedistMode.name: agentOspfv3RouteRedistMode
agentOspfv3RouteRedistMode.description: User enabels/disables route-redistribution for a particular source protocol.

agentOspfv3RouteRedistMetric.name: agentOspfv3RouteRedistMetric
agentOspfv3RouteRedistMetric.description: Metric used for redistributing a particular source protocol route into OSPF.

agentOspfv3RouteRedistMetricConfigured.name: agentOspfv3RouteRedistMetricConfigured
agentOspfv3RouteRedistMetricConfigured.description: Flag to determine whether OSPF redistribute-metric is configured or not.

agentOspfv3RouteRedistMetricType.name: agentOspfv3RouteRedistMetricType
agentOspfv3RouteRedistMetricType.description: Metric Type of routes,which OSPF redistributes from other source protocols. It can be 1(external type 1) or 2(external type 2).

agentOspfv3RouteRedistTag.name: agentOspfv3RouteRedistTag
agentOspfv3RouteRedistTag.description: It specifies the tag field in routes redistributed by OSPF.

agentOspfv3IfTable.name: agentOspfv3IfTable
agentOspfv3IfTable.description: The OSPF Interface Table describes the inter- faces from the viewpoint of OSPF. Augments ospfIfTable from the OSPF-MIB.

agentOspfv3IfEntry.name: agentOspfv3IfEntry
agentOspfv3IfEntry.description: The OSPF Interface Entry describes one inter- face from the viewpoint of OSPF. Augments ospfIfEntry in OSPF-MIB.

agentOspfv3IfIpMtuIgnoreFlag.name: agentOspfv3IfIpMtuIgnoreFlag
agentOspfv3IfIpMtuIgnoreFlag.description: Configures the IP MTU Ignore Flag value for this OSPF interface.

agentOspfv3IfPassiveMode.name: agentOspfv3IfPassiveMode
agentOspfv3IfPassiveMode.description: Flag to determine whether the interface is passive. A passive interface will not participate in the OSPF adjacency formation.

agentOspfv3LsdbTable.name: agentOspfv3LsdbTable
agentOspfv3LsdbTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Adver- tisements
agentOspfv3LsdbTable.description: The OSPF Process's Link State Database.

agentOspfv3LsdbAreaId.name: agentOspfv3LsdbAreaId
agentOspfv3LsdbAreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
agentOspfv3LsdbAreaId.description: The 32 bit identifier of the Area from which the LSA was received.

agentOspfv3LsdbType.name: agentOspfv3LsdbType
agentOspfv3LsdbType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.1 The Link State Advertisement header
agentOspfv3LsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertise- ment format.

agentOspfv3LsdbLsid.name: agentOspfv3LsdbLsid
agentOspfv3LsdbLsid.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.4 Link State ID
agentOspfv3LsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP Address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

agentOspfv3LsdbRouterId.name: agentOspfv3LsdbRouterId
agentOspfv3LsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters
agentOspfv3LsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

agentOspfv3LsdbSequence.name: agentOspfv3LsdbSequence
agentOspfv3LsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number
agentOspfv3LsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and dupli- cate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

agentOspfv3LsdbAge.name: agentOspfv3LsdbAge
agentOspfv3LsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state adver- tisement in seconds.

agentOspfv3LsdbChecksum.name: agentOspfv3LsdbChecksum
agentOspfv3LsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connec- tionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

agentOspfv3LsdbAdvertisement.name: agentOspfv3LsdbAdvertisement
agentOspfv3LsdbAdvertisement.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Adver- tisements
agentOspfv3LsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

agentOspfv3AutoCostRefBw.name: agentOspfv3AutoCostRefBw
agentOspfv3AutoCostRefBw.description: Auto cost refernece bandwidth of the router interafaces for ospf metric calculations. It can be an integer from 1 to 4294967. The default reference bandwidth is 100 Mbps.

agentOspfv3AsLsdbTable.name: agentOspfv3AsLsdbTable
agentOspfv3AsLsdbTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Adver- tisements
agentOspfv3AsLsdbTable.description: The OSPF Process's AS-scope LSA Link State Database. The Database contains the AS-scope Link State Advertisements from throughout the areas that the device is attached to. This table is identical to the OSPF LSDB Table in format, but contains only AS-scope Link State Advertisements. The purpose is to allow AS-scope LSAs to be displayed once for the router rather than once in each non-stub area.

agentOspfv3AsLsdbType.name: agentOspfv3AsLsdbType
agentOspfv3AsLsdbType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.1 The Link State Advertisement header
agentOspfv3AsLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertise- ment format.

agentOspfv3AsLsdbLsid.name: agentOspfv3AsLsdbLsid
agentOspfv3AsLsdbLsid.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.4 Link State ID
agentOspfv3AsLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP Address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

agentOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.name: agentOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId
agentOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters
agentOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

agentOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.name: agentOspfv3AsLsdbSequence
agentOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number
agentOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It starts with the value '80000001'h, or -'7FFFFFFF'h, and increments until '7FFFFFFF'h. Thus, a typical sequence number will be very negative. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

agentOspfv3AsLsdbAge.name: agentOspfv3AsLsdbAge
agentOspfv3AsLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state adver- tisement in seconds.

agentOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum.name: agentOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum
agentOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connec- tionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

agentOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement.name: agentOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement
agentOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement.reference: OSPF Version 3, Section 12 Link State Adver- tisements. Note that for variable length LSAs, SNMP agents may not be able to return the largest string size.
